collectionMetadata.name: Preventive Health Screening Statistics
collectionMetadata.description:
1) Percentage of Primary 1 and equivalent age groups medically screened
2) Percentage of women aged 50 to 69 years who have gone for Mammography
in the last 2 years
3) Percentage of women aged 25 to 69 years who have Pap Smear done in the last 3 years

Source for 2) and 3): Health Behaviour Surveillance Survey (HBSS) series, which has been discontinued. Next update will be from the National Population Health Survey (NPHS) 2019, which will be ready in late 2020.

datasetMetadata.name: Percentage of Women Aged 25 to 69 Years Who have Pap Smear Done in the Last 3 Years
datasetMetadata.description:
Percentage of women aged 25 to 69 years who have pap smear done in the last 3 years

Notes		
1. Data for years 2010 to 2016 is from Health Behaviour Surveillance Survey (HBSS) series, which has been discontinued, while data for 2019 was collected from the National Population Health Survey (NPHS) 2019, which is a new series of health survey.	
2. Data for years 2010 to 2016 are based on adults aged 25 to 69 years, while data for 2019 is based on adults aged 25 to 74 years.

datasetMetadata.name: Percentage of Women Aged 50 to 69 Years Who have gone for Mammography in the Last 2 Years
datasetMetadata.description:
Percentage of women aged 50 to 69 years who have gone for mammography in the last 2 years

Notes		
1. Data for years 2010 to 2016 is from Health Behaviour Surveillance Survey (HBSS) series, which has been discontinued, while data for 2019 was collected from the National Population Health Survey (NPHS) 2019, which is a new series of health survey.

datasetMetadata.name: Percentage of Primary 1 and Equivalent Age Groups Medically Screened
datasetMetadata.description:
Percentage of Primary 1 and equivalent age groups medically screened

Notes			
1. Data for years 2010 to 2016 is from Health Behaviour Surveillance Survey (HBSS) series, which has been discontinued, while data for 2019 was collected from the National Population Health Survey (NPHS) 2019, which is a new series of health survey.		
2. Data for years 2010 to 2016 are based on adults aged 25 to 69 years, while data for 2019 is based on adults aged 25 to 74 years.		
3. Significant decrease in no. of P1 students screened in 2020 and 2021 due to disruption of Primary School health screening.
